review_blob: So much orange! The orange flavor and aroma overpower this Ipa. It isnt bad, there is an interesting bitterness at the end. But too much citrus for me liking.
From a can, poured into a pint glass. Beautiful amber color with a nice lacy head. Very light and refreshing taste.
beer_name: Moab Brewery Dead Horse Amber Ale

review_blob: From bottle. Super hoppy, but nice. You can instantly taste the alcohol, but in a really nice way. A really good IPA.
Pours really light with a good head. At first the citrus taste is overpowering, but after letting it settle, it is a really good lager.
Very malty, starts really well, but the taste falls off dramatically. The low alcohol content makes this feel very light.
From a bottle, pint glass. Light pour, not heavily carbonated. Citrus aroma, also, tastes heavily of grapefruit. Very good summer beer.
This is really good. Nice aroma, easy to drink and light for an IPA. I?m pleasantly surprised.

Nice pour, dark brown color. Small, tan head. Smells of roasted malt, coffee and a little chocolate. Not bad, but Im not really feeling the nitro thing. I love nitros at the bar, but this just seems average.
Pretty boring, which was in itself, surprising. I was expecting more. Its just an average, ok Ipa.
This has a nice color and a nice initial taste. Then the citrus hits and the bitterness comes on strong. A little off for me, but not bad.
This is a great double IPA from a great brewer. It?s delicious and easy to drink. The hops are flavorful without being overpowering. Enjoy!
beer_name: Squatters Hop Rising Double India Pale Ale

review_blob: This is such a delicious IPA. Seriously surprising. Its not overpowering, but just right. One of the best Ive ever had.
